		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">jesperj wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It would be so cool if you could somehow connect a cable to the connectors of a cartridge, so data would go from the cable to the NES and not through some chips on the cartridge board, and then hook that cable to a computer somehow, i guess through a serial or parallell (or usb or whatever) port, and then have a way to talk to the nes through the computer. <br /></div>
<br />
<br />I remember someone a long time ago talking about an idea like that, I think as an ISA card.. maybe it was on the old forums.
<br />
<br />The thing is, the latency needed would be extremely low.  There's gonna have to be some hardware in the interface somewhere, because I don't think software could be fast enough to handle it just yet.
<br />
<br />Maybe the closest thing to what you want is an EPROM emulator.

		

