	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A lot of people would like a card with 128 KB of PRG RAM, 8 KB of CHR RAM, a few KB of ROM to bootstrap the thing, and an UNROM-style mapper (with bit 3 selecting ROM or RAM in the upper 16 KB). Connect a cable from the PC's parallel or serial port to the NES's controller port, and you have multiboot just like on the GBA.
<br />
<br />Or you could get an FDS RAM card and an FDS Loader cable, which has much the same idea as what I presented.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


